revision.text:
'''ANSI C12.10''' is the [[ANSI]] ''American National Standard for Physical Aspects of Watt-hour Meters''.<ref>{{cite web |title=NEMA releases two revised standards |date=November 1, 2004 |publisher=[[Plant Engineering]] |url=http://www.plantengineering.com/index.php?id=1792&cHash=081010&tx_ttnews%5Btt_news%5D=32522|accessdate=November 25, 2012}}</ref>
This standard covers the physical aspects of both detachable and bottom-connected [[watt-hour]] [[electricity meter|meters]] and associated registers. These include ratings, internal wiring arrangements, pertinent dimensions, markings and other general specifications.<ref>{{cite web|title=American National Standard for Physical Aspects of Watthour Meters—Safety Standard |date=2004 |publisher=NEMA |url=http://www.nema.org/stds/c12-10.cfm |accessdate=November 25, 2009 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090328133725/http://www.nema.org/stds/c12-10.cfm |archivedate=March 28, 2009 }}</ref> This standard includes references to latest version of ANSI C12.1 and ANSI C12.20 for performance requirements. Dimensions and other relevant specifications have been coordinated with ANSIC12.7-2005 American National Standard Requirements for Watthour Meters Sockets.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.thomasnet.com/companystory/NEMA-publishes-watthour-meter-safety-standard-604987|title=NEMA Publishes ANSINEMA C12.10 Physical Aspects of Watthour Meters-Safety Standard}}</ref>
