'''HVDC SylWin1''' is a [[high voltage direct current]] (HVDC) link under construction to transmit [[Offshore wind power]] to the [[power grid]] of the [[Germany|German mainland]]. The project differs from most HVDC systems in that one of the two [[HVDC converter station|converter stations]] is built on a platform in the sea. [[HVDC converter#Voltage-Sourced Converter|Voltage-Sourced Converters]] with DC ratings of 864&nbsp;MW, ±320&nbsp;kV are used and the total cable length is 205&nbsp;km. The project is similar to the [[HVDC BorWin2]] project but has slightly higher power and voltage ratings. It is being built by the [[Siemens]]/ [[Prysmian Group|Prysmian]] consortium and was handed over to its owner, [[TenneT]], in April 2015.<ref>[https://www.offshorewind.biz/2015/04/27/tennet-takes-over-sylwin1-offshore-grid-connection/ TenneT Takes Over SylWin1 Offshore Grid Connection], Offshore Wind.biz, 27 April 2015.</ref>
